description:
Responsibilities:

Take lead in gathering business requirements and agree with stakeholders on the final solution
Work with IT and other departments to translate business requirements and proposed solution into development plan
Model and design solution or alternatives, evaluate solution proposals under consideration of architectural standards, FinTech strategy, current business process and constraints;
Ability to analyse complex systems requirement; strong analytical and conceptual skills, quality awareness;
Ensure the solution designed can both benefiting the business while the post-production maintenance is catered
Take part in the change management and the evolution of system after implementation.

Requirements:

Bachelor degree or above, master degree is a plus;
Min. 5 years of relevant experience in project management, securities brokerage, wealth management and other digital/FinTech applications;
Good innovative mindset; capable of designing the features of FinTech systems;
With relevant business/technical analysis experience and good understanding in large-scale financial technology implementation in wealth management and related experience
Able to work under pressure, exhibit a high level of integrity, a strong sense of accountability, excellent communication skills and a good team player
Excellent command in spoken and written Mandarin, Cantonese and English


We offer an attractive remuneration package to the right candidate. Interested parties please forward your full resume with availability, expected salary by pressing "Apply now" or send it to 27/F., Low Block, Grand Millennium Plaza, 181 Queen’s Road, Central, Hong Kong.

(Data collected will be kept strictly confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.)

Responsibilities:

Conduct feasibility studies and due diligence, and prepare proposal and presentation for various types of business transactions;
Co-ordinate with internal departments and external parties for projects and transactions;
Assist in planning, structuring and execution for projects and transaction; and
Perform ad hoc duties as assigned

Requirements:

Degree holder in Finance, Accounting or related discipline; preferably with relevant postgraduate/ professional qualifications such as CFA or CPA;
At least 2 years’ relevant experience in business analysis, financial modelling, corporate planning; Aviation experience preferred;
Exposure in PRC/ multi-jurisdiction transaction/ contract review is desirable;
Proactive, result oriented, organized, able to work under a dynamic high growth environment with solid proficiency in business analytical skills;
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese (including Mandarin); 
Proficient in MS office including Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing; and
Candidate with more experience would be considered as Senior Financial Analyst.

Job Responsibilities:
1, Taking part in the process of establishing and deepening relationships with  current and potential investors;
2, Dealing with potential investors’ process of commercial and financial due  diligence;
3, Building Business Plan, financial models, and other documents in dataroom;
4, Broadening partnerships with relating third-party institutions and top-tier investment institutions.
 
Job Requirements:
1, At least Master Degree in Finance, Accounting, or other relating fields;
2, At least 3-year working experience with big-4;
3, High level of interpersonal skills;
4, Solid financial analytical skills;
5, Self-motivated with a proven ability to manage multiple tasks.

Responsibility:

Assist in conducting business planning, project evaluation, valuation and financial analysis and due diligence on investment projects;
Coordinate transaction process and liaising with external parties including legal counsel, regulatory entities, etc.;
Assist in devising financing solutions for procuring capital for new development projects;
Assist in negotiation and liaison with financial institutions and relevant parties in terms of financing and transactions;
Provide support in asset management of the investment portfolios and delivery of project business plans;
Handle ad hoc projects from time to time.
Requirement:

Qualified degree in finance, accounting, economics or related discipline;
Holder of a recognized professional accounting or finance qualification is an advantage;
At least 2 years of relevant experiences;
Banking / IFA / Insurance Company experience and track record on financing and investment projects is definitely an advantage;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
Good command in written and spoken English and Chinese including Mandarin;
Self-motivated, result oriented and able to work under a dynamic high growth environment.
